Consumer complaint narrative:
Let me first say, that I have tried to reach out to them ( Chase Freedom Credit Card ) many many times. All of these communication attempts were not successful. The problem began XXXX months ago. At the time, I had XXXX credit cards with Chase Bank. that would be this card, and Chase XXXX Business Preferred Card. But what occurred was as follows. Following XXXX larger purchases, XXXX for a rent payment of {$1100.00} and another for a computer purchase, around {$630.00}. It was advertised on their site, that I could elect a " my chase plan ''. With this plan, I would be paying these charges off, over 6 or 12 months. at the time, I thought this was a good idea. I did not know how wrong I would be. 

The balances were never taken off of the full principal balances, as advertised. Also, nowhere in their language on their website, did it indicate that once signed up for, the " My Chase Plan '' can not EVER be reversed. I tried to do this several times, to no avail. I spoke to a rep there, then supervisors. I spoke to a supervisor in XXXX. This manager stated " You can find a balance transfer card, if you would like, to avoid the interest charges that will accrue. I did this after my last wedding. I said 'interest charges, nope ' '' He actually said that. Later that next week, I spoke to another supervisor, who refused to undo the my chase plans. With these two my chase plans, I could no longer afford to pay my minimum payments. In effect, the payments were now about {$390.00} in total. 
I had asked them about payment assistance. They would not offer me that number, ever, so I could contact them directly. Again, the party line became, we can not reverse these my chase plans, sorry. I submitted an executive complaint, with them, and with my local branch, in XXXX XXXX, CA. I got a call XXXX days later, that again, they could do nothing to reverse the charges or plans on this account. But it gets worse here! 

The branch was nicer, much nicer. But after the executive complaint process, that credit line was cut, like immediately, in retaliation for the complaints. I had to contact XXXX XXXX XXXX about this issue, and apply for a XXXX XXXX XXXX. That reduced the monthly payment to {$190.00}, but I can not even afford that, with my rent being so high ( $ XXXX ). Just this Sunday, I learned that the Chase XXXX card had been cancelled as well. I spoke to a supervisor on that day, who stated that I was a " high risk '' and that b/c of the DMP, this credit line was closed, and could not be re-opened. 

so... Here I am submitting this complaint. I have been totally broke, and overdrawn since Sunday. I almost actually had a XXXX the other day, on an errand to go get food. And had to go to the ER yesterday. They did XXXX CTs and blood tests to rule out a transient ischemic XXXX. I am not kidding when I say this has all created a ton of XXXX for me, both financially and emotionally. Now, did I spend too much on these cards= YES. Was I irresponsible at times? Yes, I was. And that is what I told the branch. But as of now, I will not be able to make the next XXXX Payment. 

All of this comes back to the unfair business practice of the My Chase Plan. If it had not been for that, I would have been able to make my minimum payments, and been out of trouble. These people at JP Chase Morgan and the credit card departments, specifically, have no interest in helping consumers out. AT ALL! They are XXXX. I wanted to submit this complaint. I am facing bankruptcy, at this point. This has really messed up my health as well. I want others to know what happened to me. So they can pay off their cards and avoid these XXXX.

Consumer complaint narrative:
Per the attached credit report, Real Time Resolutions is claiming that the debt is an active trade line. In order to be an active trade line, ownership rights need to be proven per the FCRA 15 USC 1681. Based on the prior documentation issued by your firm, only servicing rights exist. The alleged debt on the credit report is also subject to foreclosure action from 2018, which means the debt should listed as charged off. Moreover, RTR never filed a claim on the foreclosure funds available post first lien claim. Such action makes the gross amount reported erroneous. Per the FCRA 15 USC1681 -2a ( 1 ), there is a requirement to report all information based on total accuracy. The information reported has been inaccurate in the past and conflicts with prior disclosure issued. Per the FCRA it is also illegal to park or re-age old debt on the credit report. The Federal Trade Commission also requires that the proper and transparent information be disclosed during the collection period of a debt. 
Ownership of an alleged debt must be properly disclosed per FDCPA rule 803 ( 6 ) ( b ). Per the FDCPA and FCRA rules cited within, I am requesting that all credit trade line be eliminated.

Consumer complaint narrative: On XX/XX/XXXX, I ordered a purse from saks.com ( Saks Fifth Avenue ) and paid for it with my Saks store credit card issued by Capital XXXX. It was order # XXXX. The total purchase was {$390.00}. The purse arrived two days later and I immediately decided to return it- it was not quite what I had expected. I returned it exactly according to Saks procedure, and my account indicated several days later that the return had been received. To date, despite many, many, many phone calls and emails to both Saks and Capital One, I have not been issued a credit. I have received verbal and written apologies for the delay and assurances that the credit would be posted, but there is still no credit. Since the beginning of the pandemic, this is not the first time that I have experienced unreasonable delays in receiving credit from Saks for items purchased on line and then returned. It seems they are trying very hard to hold onto my money as long as possible, but two months and two billing cycles is inexcusable. And I STILL do not have my credit. Anything you can do to help me would be deeply appreciated. And if you choose to publish this information, I would certainly be OK with that because Saks needs to know that customers find this practice completely and utterly unacceptable and unethical. I am attaching a copy of an email from Saks on XX/XX/XXXX indicating that they are sorry for the delay and that a credit would be posted. I received my newest statement from Capital One on XX/XX/XXXX. There was no credit. I called Capital One and they said to wait a week to see if the credit would be posted. It has now been ten more days, still no credit. Meanwhile, I am making only minimum payments on this card because I truly do NOT owe anything to Saks. So now I am incurring interest on the amount due, which I think Saks should reimburse me for as well.

I hereby exercise my legal rights enacted by Congress and The Federal Trade Commission, which explicitly states when a victim of identity-theft dispute a fraudulent account on his/her credit report it shall be honored by all credit bureaus and all fraudulent information should be blocked within 4 days and proper notification shall be given to all data furnishers pursuant to section 605b of The Federal Fair Credit Reporting Act. Failure to comply shall lead to complaints being filed with The XXXX XXXX XXXX, Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, and Attorney General stating your companys unlawful collection practices, misrepresentation of creditworthiness, defamation of character, and noncompliance to abide by laws enacted by Congress to protect victims of identity-theft who's credit been impacted by acts of fraud. Because I know my rights under THE FAIR CREDIT REPORTING ACT, CONSUMER CREDIT PROTECTION ACT ( CCPA ), and FAIR and ACCURATE CREDIT TRANSACTION ACT of 2003 ( FACTA ). I will be taking action. I also know my rights under this paragraph of Section 312 of the FACTA LAW : SEC.312. Procedures to enhance the accuracy and integrity of information furnished to consumer reporting agencies. ( b ) duty of furnishers to provide accurate information. -- Section 623 ( a ) ( 1 ) of THE FAIR CREDIT REPORTING ACT ( 15 U.S.C. 1681s-2 ( a ) ( 1 ) is amended ( 1 ) in subparagraph ( A ), by striking " knows or consciously avoids knowing the information is inaccurate '' and inserting " knows or has reasonable cause to believe that the information is inaccurate '', and ( 2 ) by adding at the end of the following : ( D ) DEFINITION -- For purposes of subparagraph ( A ), the term 'reasonable cause to believe that the information is inaccurate ' means having specific knowledge, other than solely allegations by the consumer, that would cause a reasonable person to have substantial doubts about the accuracy of information. Policy states. According to the Fair Credit Reporting Act FCRA 611 ( 15 U.S.C 1681 ), Procedure In Case of Disputed Accuracy. ( a ) Reinvestigation ( 1 ) Reinvestigation ( a ) In general. Subject to Subsection ( f ), if the completeness or accuracy of any item of information contained in a consumers file at a consumer agency is disputed by the consumer and the consumer notifies the agency directly, or indirectly through a reseller, of such dispute, free of charge, conduct a reasonable reinvestigation to determine whether the disputed information is inaccurate and record the current status of the disputed information, or delete the item from the file in accordance with paragraph ( 5 ), before the end of the 30-day period beginning on the date on which the agency receives the notice of the dispute from the consumer or reseller. Therefore, my position is being clearly stated, these accounts do not belong to me, meaning that you are reporting inaccurate account information within my credit file. The fact that these are inaccurate account information means that you, this credit-reporting agency, are reporting incorrect accounts. 1. The Fair Credit Reporting Act requires that you, the credit-reporting agency report accurate and/or correct account information within my credit file. My credit issues are very specific, these accounts and/or items do not belong to me. This means that you are reporting incorrect account information within my credit report. It is this in mind that I request that these listed accounts and items be Blocked and Deleted. According to the Fair Credit Reporting Act FCRA, Section 1681c ( 2 ) Block of information resulting from identity theft. 1.Block. Except as otherwise provided in this section, a consumer reporting shall block the reporting of any information in the file of a consumer that the consumer identifies as information that resulted from alleged identity theft, not later than four ( 4 ) business days after the date receipt by such agency of 1. Consumer complaint narrative:
MANIPULATION OF FORECLOSURE AUCTION, FORGED FORECLOSURE PUBLICATIONS AND MALICIOUS OBSTRUCTION OF HOMEOWNER 'S RIGHT TO DUE PROCESS This situation has been a long and exhausting process which originated when the mortgage on the property contained an incorrect legal description. In attempting to foreclose on the property, BNY Mellon intentionally forged the legal description on the Court documents publicizing the auction instead of reforming the mortgage as it is required to do, by law and which resulted in a grossly inadequate bid price. 

Further, in an effort to settle the matter, I attempted, on multiple occasions, to satisfy the entire foreclosure judgment. BNY Mellon refused to accept full payment and instead accepted almost half of the judgment amount from a known collusive bidder in a grossly faulty foreclosure auction. 

After BNY Mellon forged Court filed documents to avoid correcting the mortgage, it then maliciously prevented me from satisfying the judgment, retaining the equity in my home, and satisfying the judgment to avoid a completed foreclosure. They also conspired with the auction bidder to prevent my right to due process and hearing of my timely objections to the faulty foreclosure auction. 

I have raised these issues in a multi-year court battle ; yet BNY Mellon continues to engage in knowingly malicious bad acts. They have admitted their errors in XXXX documents, yet they refuse to take corrective actions. It is unacceptable and must be addressed. It has cost me years of my life, tremendous financial distress and the loss of home in spite of my multiple, assertive efforts to satisfy the full judgment.
Company: BANK OF NEW YORK MELLON CORPORATION, THE

Consumer complaint narrative: RE : Attentively review my formal writ composed declaration of not proven complaint misinformation that is all or in part : deficient of the adequate current status in the fullness of TRUTH, ACCURACY, COMPLETENESS, TIMELINESS, documented OWNERSHIP, certifiable RESPONSIBILITY, or otherwise irrefutable, complaint obligatory, and regulatory requisite reporting thereby mandating your immediate actions to rectify and remedy and any infractions behavior ( s ) by retaining or returning to demonstrate TRUE, CORRECT, COMPLETE, and COMPLAINT METRO 2 data field formatted reporting!!! I am a victim of identity- theft, I am writing to request that you block all accounts disputed as fraudulent on my credit reports with XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX and XXXX This information does not relate to any transactions I have made. I did not give anyone authorization or consent to use my personal information. I hereby exercise my legal rights enacted by Congress and The Federal Trade Commission, which explicitly states when a victim of identity-theft dispute a fraudulent account on his/her credit report it shall be honored by all credit bureaus and all fraudulent information should be blocked within 4 days and proper notification shall be given to all data furnishers pursuant to section 605b of The Federal Fair Credit Reporting Act. Failure to comply shall lead to complaints being filed with XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, and Attorney General stating your companys unlawful collection practices, misrepresentation of creditworthiness, defamation of character, and noncompliance to abide by laws enacted by Congress to protect victims of identity-theft who's credit been impacted by acts of fraud. Because I know my rights under THE FAIR CREDIT REPORTING ACT, CONSUMER CREDIT PROTECTION ACT ( CCPA ), and FAIR and ACCURATE CREDIT TRANSACTION ACT of 2003 ( FACTA ). I will be taking action. I also know my rights under this paragraph of Section 312 of the FACTA LAW : SEC.312. Procedures to enhance the accuracy and integrity of information furnished to consumer reporting agencies. ( b ) duty of furnishers to provide accurate information. -- Section 623 ( a ) ( 1 ) of THE FAIR CREDIT REPORTING ACT ( 15 U.S.C. 1681s-2 ( a ) ( 1 ) is amended ( 1 ) in subparagraph ( A ), by striking " knows or consciously avoids knowing the information is inaccurate '' and inserting " knows or has reasonable cause to believe that the information is inaccurate '', and ( 2 ) by adding at the end of the following : ( D ) DEFINITION -- For purposes of subparagraph ( A ), the term 'reasonable cause to believe that the information is inaccurate ' means having specific knowledge, other than solely allegations by the consumer, that would cause a reasonable person to have substantial doubts about the accuracy of information. Policy states. According to the Fair Credit Reporting Act FCRA 611 ( 15 U.S.C 1681 ), Procedure In Case of Disputed Accuracy. ( a ) Reinvestigation ( 1 ) Reinvestigation ( a ) In general. Subject to Subsection ( f ), if the completeness or accuracy of any item of information contained in a consumers file at a consumer agency is disputed by the consumer and the consumer notifies the agency directly, or indirectly through a reseller, of such dispute, free of charge, conduct a reasonable reinvestigation to determine whether the disputed information is inaccurate and record the current status of the disputed information, or delete the item from the file in accordance with paragraph ( 5 ), before the end of the 30-day period beginning on the date on which the agency receives the notice of the dispute from the consumer or reseller. Therefore, my position is being clearly stated, these accounts do not belong to me, meaning that you are reporting inaccurate account information within my credit file. The fact that these are inaccurate account information means that you, this credit-reporting agency, are reporting incorrect accounts. 1. CAPITAL ONE bal. {$0.00} I am well aware of my rights as a consumer. The Fair Credit Reporting Act requires that you, the credit-reporting agency report accurate and/or correct account information within my credit file. My credit issues are very specific, these accounts and/or items do not belong to me. This means that you are reporting incorrect account information within my credit report. It is this in mind that I request that these listed accounts and items be Blocked and Deleted. According to the Fair Credit Reporting Act FCRA, Section 1681c ( 2 ) Block of information resulting from identity theft. 1.Block. Except as otherwise provided in this section, a consumer reporting shall block the reporting of any information in the file of a consumer that the consumer identifies as information that resulted from alleged identity theft, not later than four ( 4 ) business days after the date receipt by such agency of 1. Appropriate proof of identity of the consumer ; 2. A copy of an identity theft report 3. The identification of such information by the consumer ; and 4. A statement by the consumer that the information relating to the transaction by the consumer. I have provided all of the above listed four ( 4 ) items within this package. Therefore, I expect these listed accounts to be deleted and blocked within ( 4 ) business days. This is clearly an identity theft issue. I am also entitled to receive a free copy of my credit report, so I am requesting a free credit report and that all of these accounts, public records items, and inquiries be permanently blocked and deleted. Enclosures : Identity Theft Report Proof of Identity Copy of Account Statement showing Fraudulent Items FTC Notice to Furnishers CC : Consumer Financial Protection Bureau XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXXXXXX, Iowa XXXX

Consumer complaint narrative:
On XX/XX/2023, I deposited {$1700.00} into the atm at Citizens bank in XXXX, RI. The ATM returned {$20.00} then said there was an error. The ATM tried to return the rest of the money and you could hear it trying but nothing came out. When I tried to ask it to return the money it said an error has occurred but no receipt came out or error paperwork. The money ( {$1600.00} ) was never credited to my account. I called the bank while at the ATM and they said they would call me within 24 hours. I never received a call. My boyfriend and I called on XX/XX/2023 and spoke with someone. They said no one was suppose to call us and they need to count the ATM. However, on XX/XX/2023, the branch where the error happened, a technician went to the atm that morning. So, they did send someone out there. I found this out by calling the branch on XX/XX/2023. I spoke with a supervisor at Citizens Customer Service named XXXX. He said they put an expedited claim in but they still havent contacted us or anything. We havent had our account credited or anything. We got the feeling that unless we really push this, we wont be returned the money. That money was from both our jobs and is meant for our bills that we are now late on. We called our car insurance to try and explain the situation. They understood but couldnt promise anything like our insurance lapsing. Which will cost us extra money. 
The atm has cameras so they should be able to see everything that happened in case there is an error with the atms software and it doesnt report the logs properly.

In XXXX, I applied for and received the XXXX credit card after viewing a website advertisement claiming you can get 3 % on your top spend category, 2 % on your second, and 1 % on everything else. This is not made clear to someone who is interested even when they click on the " learn more '' link. " Other '' is clearly listed as a category you can earn rewards on without further disclosure that you can only earn 1 %, and that it is treated differently than every other category listed. 

After I found in the XXXX app that I would not earn 3 % on the " other '' category I went back to the website to do the research. I found that once you click on " learn more '' you are taken to the following link XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX On that page it shows " other '' as a category you can earn rewards on. Right below, there is a heading saying " Rake in the rewards ''. Underneath the heading it states, " The XXXX Credit Card gives you custom cash back* rewards maximized to what you spend the most on. Well track your spend categories as they change, so you can just sit back and cash in. '' I scrolled to the bottom of the page to read the asterisk, which states, " * Use of cash back is subject to the terms of the XXXX account. Review the XXXX Credit Card Rewards Program Terms for more information. '' I then clicked on the link to the " rewards program terms '' taking me to this page : hXXXX XXXX XXXX This link has no information at all on the 3 %, 2 %, or 1 % rewards and how they work. It only describes how the credit card works and things like interest. 

To me, and probably a lot of other customers, this appears that XXXX is trying to hide the facts.

This letter is regarding account # XXXX, which you claim I owe {$230.00}. This is a formal notice that your claim is disputed.

Please note that I am requesting " validation '' ; that is competent evidence bearing my signature, showing that I have ( or ever had ) some contractual obligation to pay you. 

Please also be aware that any negative mark found on my credit reports ( including Experian, XXXX and XXXX ) from your company or any company that you represent, for a debt that I don't owe, is a violation of the FCRA & FDCPA ; therefore if you can not validate the debt, you must request that all credit reporting agencies delete the entry. 

Pending the outcome of my investigation of any evidence that you submit, you are instructed to take no action that could be detrimental to any of my credit reports. 

Failure to respond within 30 days of receipt of this certified letter will result in small claims legal action against your company at my local venue. I will be seeking a minimum of {$1000.00} in damages per violation for : 1. ) Defamation 2. ) Negligent Enablement of Identity Fraud 3. ) Violation of the Fair Debt Collection Practices Act ( including but not limited to Section 807-8 ) 4. ) Violation of the Fair Credit Reporting Act ( including but not limited to Section 623-b ) Please Note : This notice is an attempt to correct your records, and any information received from you will be collected as evidence should any further action be necessary. This is a request for information only, and is not a statement, election, or waiver of status. 


P.S. Please be aware that dependent upon your response, I may be detailing any potential issues with your company via an online public press release, including documentation of any potential small claims action. Consumer complaint narrative:
Hello, I am writing to dispute several violations of federal laws committed by the creditor regarding my credit report. I am extremely frustrated and emotionally distressed due to the negative impact these violations have had on my life. 

My correct name is XXXX XXXX but bureaus are reporting it as a XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, XXXX, XXXX XXXX, XXXX XXXX. Also my current address is XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, Kansas XXXX, But bureau reported that I have many addresses like XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, KS XXXX, XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, KS XXXX, XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX KS XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, NH XXXX XX/XX/XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, NH XXXX XX/XX/XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, NJ XXXX XX/XX/XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, MA XXXX XX/XX/XXXX, XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX MA XXXX XX/XX/XXXX, XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, IA XXXX XX/XX/XXXX, XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, MA XXXX XXXX And My Wrong Employers is XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX. 

The creditor has reported inaccurate information on my credit report, including multiple addresses that I have never lived at. These inaccuracies have affected my credit score, and have made it difficult for me to obtain credit and loans at reasonable rates. The creditor has violated several federal laws including : Fair Credit Reporting Act ( FCRA ) - 15 U.S.C. 1681e ( b ) - This section requires credit reporting agencies to follow reasonable procedures to ensure the accuracy of the information in a consumer 's credit report. The inaccurate reporting of multiple addresses may be a violation of this section. 
Fair Debt Collection Practices Act ( FDCPA ) - 15 U.S.C. 1692e - This section prohibits debt collectors from using false, deceptive, or misleading representations in the collection of a debt. Reporting inaccurate addresses may be a violation of this section if the debt collector knew or should have known that the information was false or misleading. 
Fair and Accurate Credit Transactions Act ( FACTA ) - 15 U.S.C. 6821 - This section requires businesses to implement reasonable policies and procedures to protect sensitive consumer information from unauthorized access or disclosure. The failure to protect sensitive consumer information resulting in inaccurate reporting of multiple addresses may be a violation of this section. 
Truth in Lending Act ( TILA ) - 15 U.S.C. 1601 et seq. - This law requires lenders to provide borrowers with certain disclosures about credit terms and costs. While the reporting of multiple addresses is not a direct violation of TILA, it may be a violation if the incorrect reporting is tied to an inaccurate disclosure of credit terms or costs. 
Real Estate Settlement Procedures Act ( RESPA ) - 12 U.S.C. 2601 et seq. - This law requires mortgage lenders to provide certain disclosures to borrowers and prohibits certain practices, such as kickbacks for referrals. Reporting incorrect addresses could be a violation of RESPA if it is tied to a failure to provide required disclosures or if it is tied to a kickback scheme. 
Equal Credit Opportunity Act ( ECOA ) - 15 U.S.C. 1691 et seq. - This law prohibits lenders from discriminating against borrowers on the basis of certain protected characteristics, such as race, gender, or age. Reporting incorrect addresses could be a violation of ECOA if it results in a lender using inaccurate information to make a discriminatory decision. 
Fair Credit Billing Act ( FCBA ) - 15 U.S.C. 1666 et seq. - This law requires credit card issuers to provide certain billing error resolution procedures to cardholders. While the reporting of multiple addresses is not a direct violation of the FCBA, it could be a violation if it is tied to a failure to properly handle a billing error dispute. 
These violations have caused me significant financial harm and emotional distress. I have been denied credit and loans, and have been forced to pay higher interest rates due to the inaccurate reporting. It has also caused me significant stress and XXXX as I feel like my financial security and future opportunities have been compromised. 

I request that you enforce the legal provisions that have been violated, and that the creditor be required to remove the unverified accounts from my credit report. I also request that the creditor be held accountable for the financial and emotional harm they have caused me. 

Thank you for your time and attention to this matter. 

Sincerely, XXXX XXXX

Consumer complaint narrative: I shared a lease for my wife at the times XXXX XXXX. In XXXX of 2020, during the COVID lockdown, we had both been furloughed from our jobs and were unable to make payments on the car during that time. Before we were late with a payment, she called XXXX to ask if they would be willing to pause our payments until we were able to pay again. They agreed and had done it with many customers already. We were grateful. In XXXX of 2020 ( do not remember the exact day ), I had just been able to get back to doing some work and received multiple calls from XXXX that informed me that we were late on our payments. I asked my wife to call them and ask if there was a problem. She called and the XXXX representative told her they were automated calls about being late and to ignore them as we had paused our payments only about a month earlier. I continued to receive these automated calls over the following weeks so I called XXXX personally to ask them to stop calling. At this point the representative informed me that the payment pause was only for one month and if we wanted to extend it we would have needed to call in again. This was absolutely not made clear at the time of the pause. and then on top of that, we were told to ignore the late payment calls. How are we supposed to know if a XXXX representative is telling us accurate information or not? We made the mistake of assuming they were giving us credible information and we ended up being hit with a 30 day late note on our reports. I had never over many years with XXXX been late with a payment. And as soon as I called and spoke with the representative, I paid the entire back balance ( two months ) along with the remainder of the lease ( ended up totaling about 4 months of payments ) immediately on the phone with him. I then wrote XXXX explaining this situation and they told me they would not correct it. This is deceptive and during a time like COVID lockdown where people needed help, XXXX offered help and then punished us for accepting it. It was the wrong way to handle the situation.

Consumer complaint narrative: Once again I have found the need to seek resolve for the same issue that I just recently submitted a complaint about. In fact it seems to be the only way that I am able to get an adequate response in order to find closure so that I can move forward. It wasnt until I submitted my complaint to your agency regarding the reversal of a provisional credit, that I was granted the credit and notified that it was issued and it was final. Ironically speaking, on XXXX XXXX, on or about these dates, my account had finally been credited for two other payments that had also previously been disputed. At that time I was told to be sure to complete the forms that were to be sent to me, and return them as soon as possible. As time went on, there were no forms that arrived in the mail, only XXXX different debit cards, two of which I had never requested. It wasnt until after the previous complaint was filed that got the attention of XXXX, of US Bank, XXXX XXXX XXXX, Office of the President, who responded to the complaint by sending me documents regarding the prior complaint that notified me that the credit was granted and that it would be final, but also the documents that were never sent regarding the provisional credits that were issued on XXXX XXXX? Now mind you, the documents that were included in the packet were not only inclusive of the resolution regarding the complaint sent to your agency, but the documents that were supposed to have been sent weeks ago regarding the claims for the provisional credits that were given at the beginning of XXXX! The letter was dated XX/XX/2022 mentioned, the post mark on the outside of the envelope was dated XX/XX/2022, but the correspondence that pertained to the previous provisional credits issued the beginning of XXXX, stated that after the forms were completed they were to be sent back and received by them by XX/XX/XXXX. ( the very next day ) or the credits would be reversed! In whos reality does this exist? Certainly not in mine. First and foremost, I never received the packet until XX/XX/XXXX and at that time I did as I was instructed to do. Without any warning, on Friday, XX/XX/XXXX, I withdrew XXXX $ from my account at XXXXXXXX XXXX. and at that time my balance was as it should have been. It wasnt until approximately XXXXXXXX XXXX. that I checked my balance and the credits had been reversed resulting in a negative balance depleting my account leaving me with a negative {$680.00}! causing checks to be returned and essentially nothing at all to pay bills, get gas or food. Not only that, but the order in which things were done were not only deliberate and insulting but were done in direct retaliation because of the complaint that was filed about the claim that they had previously denied. It is obvious that the documents that were sent to me on the 15th, were not going to arrive in enough time to be returned by the XXXX. because they were sent through the regular mail and not overnight express. I have the envelope that has the postmark as well as the documents that were dated XX/XX/XXXX, requesting that they be returned by the 16th. Absolutely absurd. I have suffered an extremely emotional and financial crisis as a result of the recent deliberate unacceptable events. I am deeply concerned about the actions of a company that claims to be concerned about XXXX Veterans, which my husband proudly is but given the most recent unethical behavior that has been disclosed involving US Bank employees and unsuspecting customers.

On XX/XX/2020, i purchased an air plane ticket from XXXX XXXX for a two way ticket ( going XXXX  to XXXX  on XX/XX/XXXX and returning from XXXX  to Miami on XX/XX/XXXX ) via my BANK OF AMERICA PERSONAL credit card for {$260.00}. 
This was around first week when XXXX was opened air travel during coronovirus epidemic During purchase process and on their website ( XXXX ) there was no information for any additional requirements. 
I also tried to reach them ( XXXX XXXX  ) on the phone to get information for any possible restriction/requirements for traveling to XXXX during coronovirus specially this first week XXXX government opens air traveling to the country, but i was not able to reach anyone on the phone. 
I heard from a traveling person ( to an other country ) that some countries are requiring Covid 19 test. 
I went to XXXX and got a Covid -19 test incase it might make my travel less complicated. 
When i try to fly on XX/XX/XXXX from XXXX aiport, I was told in check in desk that i can not fly not only without Covid 19 - PCS test. that time i found out test that i had was not PCR test. I noticed no one else was presenting COVID 19 test during check in nor any sign or information around check in area indicates test requirements. 
Later i learned this was because XXXX  citizen living in USA are not required to have a test. it seems to me because almost everyone flying that time was XXXX  citizen, airlines did not bother to post the covid19 test requirement information for others.

I was denied flight but offered cancellation of airplane or change of flight date within 3 days of original ticket.

Knowing i can not get Covid 19 PCR test very quick, i asked for cancellation. Person in check in said they can not cancel ticket at their computer but he will put my request in system but i have to reach their customer service on the phone to complete cancellation. He also said he is changing my flight for next day in case i did get Covid 19 pcr test. It made sense to me and i left the airport. In next several weeks i tried to reach XXXX XXXX via phone chat social media even called them their customer service in XXXX but they never got back to me in mails or voice messages. On their customer service phone number, in prerecording options they ask to press for different department if inquiry is for Cancellation/refunds. then no one is available only can leave voice message. after over 1 month not getting hold of anyone for refund i contacted my credit card company, BANK OF AMERICA.. About month later i received deny letter from the bank reads : " We understand you weren't satisfied with the quality of the service the merchant provided ; however the merchant has the right to request payment for any services that were rendered " problem is i was not rendered any services. Same like you order something online but you didnt receive then you contact merchant to report but they do not respond. what happens in that case? is this just because you are not happy with their quality of service I explained to bank of America again on the phone but they seem to listen then say they will forward information to proper department to investigate. i am not able to discuss this with a bank representative who is actually handling the issue themselves. it seems they are only filling a form on computer to forward an other department which is overs implied and does not represent details of the case. Time and afford i put in this worth a lot more than actual amount in question but i want bank to take proper step to resolve the issue so XXXX XXXX stop doing this to other customers. Consumer complaint narrative:
In accordance with the fair credit reporting act. The account below has violated my federally protected consumer rights to privacy and confidentiality under 15 USC 1681. 
ACCOUNT NAME ; XXXX XXXX  ACCOUNT # XXXX 15 USC 1681 section 602 A. States I have the right to privacy. 
15 USC1681 section 604 A Section 2 ; it also states a consumer reporting agency can not furnish an account without my written instructions.

Product: Mortgage
Consumer complaint narrative:
First Issue : We purchased a XXXX property on XX/XX/XXXX with two dwellings on it : a brick ( primary ) dwelling and a mobile home ( accessory dwelling ). Both dwellings were listed for sale together. The sales contract shows that a mobile home is included ; the appraisal shows the same on 3 different pages ; the survey also shows 2 dwellings on the property. {$36000.00} of my current loan was used to pay off the initial loan for the mobile home. 

The address is different for each dwelling on the property, per county rules and regulations. The homeowners insurance carrier is different for each dwelling because we could not readily find a company that would insure both types of dwelling. Declarations pages for both policies were submitted to the initial lender, with prepayments and initial payments to both insurance companies disclosed separately at closing. 

At the first policy renewal, the mortgage company paid only the premium for the primary dwelling, citing multiple reasons over time for not adding the second company back to the escrow account. They contend that 1 ) the mobile home insurer was not included in the initial escrow statement and 2 ) there is an address mismatch, even though both dwellings are on one parcel. 

I have been calling the mortgage company since XX/XX/XXXX, when I first received an escrow account statement and a refund check, and I simultaneously received renewal declarations from primary insurer. I explained that I was confused about why I was receiving a refund, when there was still the other insurer for them to pay. I was advised to send declarations page from the primary insurer to them and send bill from the other insurer to see if it could be included in escrow. 

On XX/XX/XXXX, I was told that they were looking for the initial disclosure ; they were confirming everything with the mobile home insurer ; initial escrow was done differently ; they will need to add an additional escrow line ; by Friday everything should be updated ; they will also need to run a new analysis ; initial escrow statement is what they go by. 

On XX/XX/XXXX, another representative told me that the Insurance Department needed to rewrite the policy for the 2 dwellings on one parcel. I got transferred to someone else who asked me to upload what I had showing both addresses on the same parcel. She would transfer me to their Mortgage Customer Service for them to update the address to reflect 1 parcel with 2 addresses. The call dropped after I was transferredNo one called me back ; and when I called again, I was told that they were getting ready to generate a letter to tell me the next steps. I uploaded the Address Assignment documents from the county on XX/XX/XXXX. 
I called the insurance company again on XX/XX/XXXX. This time I was told that it looked like the mobile home insurer needed to be added ; there was a task open for that already, which was expected to close on XXXX should not have to worry about the mobile home insurer not being paid, and I could call back after XX/XX/XXXX. ( I did not disclose to them that I had already paid the mobile home insurer on XX/XX/XXXX ). I received the first request from the mortgage company in a letter dated XX/XX/XXXX, in which they requested the most recent paid receipt for homeowners insurance declaration page ( uploaded on XX/XX/XXXX and attached ). I have attached proof of both insurance policies being included at closing and in the mortgage breakdown -- including payoff of mobile home ; proof of 2 dwellings on 1 property ( one parcel ) prior to closing ; and information sent to the mortgage company as requested in XX/XX/XXXX correspondence. 

Second Issue : Besides the mediocre customer service, run-around, and lack of resolution to date, I am appalled at the deplorable service I received when I called the mortgage company on XX/XX/XXXX. I have come to know the routine by now ( after several callssometimes more than one call on a given day when the calls drop and no one calls me back, and being transferred to so many individuals ), so I was shocked when I got transferred to XXXX in the XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX that she hung up on me around XXXX! This was not a dropped call because I had the opportunity to complete the survey. She simply did not like me asking her if they did not review what I have already uploaded ( she was asking me for documents I had already sent them ). I was not nasty to her, although I will admit that I had raised my voice ( out of frustration ) I did not yell or even get loud Shame on her! Great leaders are way more professional and patient than XXXX was. How can a supervisor or manager ( someone on the Escalation Team, of all places ) behave that way? If I had been blowing my top or using foul language, then I would not have been this shocked and upset. Even if she wanted to lie and say the call dropped, why didnt she call me back, when I had just verified my telephone numberamong other things? If she did not want to help me, she could have transferred me to someone else. I am a paying customer, who has been holding up my end of the bargain by ensuring timely payments are made. The expectation from the insurance company is that they will hire and train professionals who will do their best to resolve issues in a timely mannernot add fuel to fire.

Issue: Applying for a mortgage or refinancing an existing mortgage
Consumer complaint narrative:
On XX/XX/XXXX I purchased a second home and financed it with a mortgage originated and services by JPMorgan Chase Bank ( loan number XXXX ). The home is located in Hawaii and is rented out by me or my on-island property manager when not being used by my family. My rate was 3.75 % for a 30 year fixed conventional mortgage. All payments have been made in a timely basis and I am in compliance with all requirements. 

In late XXXX I began a refinancing process with JPMorgan Chase and was quoted a rate of 2.875 % by my Chase broker XXXX XXXX ( XXXX ). All documentation was uploaded within 24-28 hours of request. The process was moving very slowly and was told Chase was backed up on refinancings. I expected to close in XXXX and that did not happen. When I inquired I was told they were waiting for condo documents. My property is part of a condo association. I repeatedly asked for updates through the month. In late XXXX I was told that the underwriter believed my property did not qualify for refinancing due to the way the property was classified. On XX/XX/XXXX I received a notice of decline. The report says the decision was made based on my credit which for the record is over XXXX with ample liquid assets. My broker told me the underwriter viewed my property as a condo-tel. It is not and I explained that. It is on a resort property in Hawaii but the condo association is independent and there is no requirement ( or option ) to rent my unit out in a rental pool at the resort. I maintain my own property manager who markets it on my behalf and if I chose not to rent it that is my choice. 

By late XXXX the underlying rates in the market increased about 100 basis points from where my rate was locked. I believe Chase, in an attempt to not honor my rate, declined my refinancing for invalid reasons. I tried appealing to no avail. What I find unusual is that Chase still owns my original loan, which 14 months old. There were no changes in our condo association rules or designations and my assets and credit remain at or better than they were a year ago. 

I was hoping someone could inquire as I believe they used unfair lending practices to avoid honoring their rate commitment to me. 

Here is my advisors contact information XXXX XXXX Home Lending Advisor NMLS # : XXXX XXXX Office XXXX XXXX ) XXXX I may be contacted at XXXX or XXXX XXXX

Let alone send me disclosures and information i am requesting? I literally have to write down all this because you are failing to correct my information? I've never heard of a company that will hide information that should be clear and easily accessible to all consumers. 

Capital one is not listening to their consumers. They are STILL not being accurate on consumer reports. And when consumers try to get information to dispute and correct them, they are making it unclear and difficult to receive the information to exercise our right to dispute.

Consumer complaint narrative: On XX/XX/2020, I purchased online a XXXX XXXX Laptop computer from Amazon. Upon receipt of the Laptop on XX/XX/2020 and after attempting to install some custom software that I use, I found that the laptop would not run my custom software programs. Laptop was reset to factory settings and laptop was returned. During this time, during the XXXX season Amazon made an arrangement with XXXX Department stores that a person could take any item that needed to be returned to XXXX and XXXX would take responsibility for the repacking and reshipping of returned items back to Amazon at no cost to the consumer. I returned the Laptop to the return dept. at our local XXXX Department store and was given a returned receipt ( which I have included a copy ) to prove my return. I had used this same service for another item I ordered online from Amazon and returned with no problem. During this time, Amazon has also sent me a gift card of which I assumed I received because I was a member of their Prime program and had ordered quite a few items from them. I did not request the gift card, they just sent it to me. I also did sign up for their credit card which I did use to purchase the laptop. The total cost came to {$300.00} Upon the return of the XXXX XXXX, I later received a bill for {$190.00} from Syncrony Bank which issues the Amazon Credit Card I used for the purchase. I called Syncrony Bank and explained that I had returned the laptop and Amazon had accepted the return. They told me that I still owned them {$190.00} for the purchase of the laptop and I should call Amazon customer support to work this out. I called Amazon and was told that I needed to clear this up with Syncrony Bank. I explained that I had already spoken to them and they had told me to call Amazon Support. To make a long story shorter, I called both sides about six times and was given hard to understand double talk about why I still owned Syncrony Bank the said amount for a laptop that I returned in good order ( factory reset ) within two days but still owed on the laptop. I was told that Amazon placed part of the return cost of the laptop into my gift card but did not cancel the balance of the return amount. I questioned Amazon about this and how exactly their gift card program works but could not decipher what the person was saying to me. ( judging by their accent, I was not speaking with anyone in the United States ). So I let it go about contacting both Amazon and Syncrony Bank because of the consistent double talk explanations. My argument is that the entire purchase that was returned should have been cancelled and if they did put some of the costs ( why they would do that I have no idea ) into the gift card they gave me, they should have explained that to me instead of automatically doing what they did without explaining it to me and automatically doing it without my permission. And although I have a high credit score, I am refusing to pay that amount of money to Syncrony Bank for a laptop that I do not have in my possession. It would be just giving my money away. So unless theres some bizarre reason that Im liable for this situation, I have not sent them any payment even though they are harassing me for payment and threatening to cause a lowering of my credit scores. In order to protect my credit scores it appears I will be forced to make payment unless something can be done to rectify this situation. I would like to have your office look into this for me. Perhaps they will give you a clearer response and explanation than I am getting from them. Ive attached screenshots of proof that I returned the item to Amazon.

I even asked them if I could find someone to take over the booking but since I was the one on the reservation they couldn't work this out. Product: Mortgage
Consumer complaint narrative:
In late XX/XX/2021, my wife and I started the process of looking for a mortgage to purchase our first home. We settled on Bank of America ( BOA ), despite our lawyer advising against it due to some bad prior experiences. However, BOA provided the lowest rate and closing cost estimate. 

Long story short, our initial mortgage officer ( NMLS # XXXX ) made various mistakes such as quoting me a different interest rate then what was actually provided. The individual was also not aware of what the processing department ( i.e., underwriters ) was doing because I had to inform the officer when the appraisal will happen and when it was done ( information my realtor provided ). Moreover, when an error occurred, the officer kept quiet and avoided responding to my emails, messages, voicemails. After all the incompetence, the officer 's manager ( NMLS # XXXX ) had to step in and take over our file. 

The situation only got worse because the manager told me I had to fire my attorney. After a couple of hours of confusion and panic, the manager told me to ignore the request. Apparently, someone at BOA thought my attorney was the bank 's attorney and did not see the name on an approved list. I also learned that it is typical of BOA to leave things to the last minute mainly because the processing department controls the show. The individual processing our file did not get to it until very last minute. My attorney and the bank 's attorney did not get the final documents until after XXXX the day before the close. There is more to the story, but I will end my complaint here. Avoid BOA for your mortgage!

Consumer complaint narrative:
In XXXX of XXXX I submitted a dispute to Experian for account XXXX XXXX XXXX, XXXX questioning the accuracy of the account. On XX/XX/XXXX, Experian removed XXXX  XXXX XXXX, XXXX. from my consumer report. In XXXX of XXXX, Experian reinserted XXXX  XXXX XXXX, XXXX. back on my consumer report. According tXXXX 15 U.S. Code 1681i ( a ) ( 5 ) ( b ) - ( 5 ) Treatment of inaccurate or unverifiable information ( A ) In general If, after any reinvestigation under paragraph ( 1 ) of any information disputed by a consumer, an item of the information is found to be inaccurate or incomplete or can not be verified, the consumer reporting agency shall ( i ) promptly delete that item of information from the file of the consumer, or modify that item of information, as appropriate, based on the results of the reinvestigation; and ( ii ) promptly notify the furnisher of that information that the information has been modified or deleted from the file of the consumer. ( B ) Requirements relating to reinsertion of previously deleted material ( i ) Certification of accuracy of information If any information is deleted from a consumers file pursuant to subparagraph ( A ), the information may not be reinserted in the file by the consumer reporting agency unless the person who furnishes the information certifies that the information is complete and accurate. 
( ii ) Notice to consumer If any information that has been deleted from a consumers file pursuant to subparagraph ( A ) is reinserted in the file, the consumer reporting agency shall notify the consumer of the reinsertion in writing not later than 5 business days after the reinsertion or, if authorized by the consumer for that purpose, by any other means available to the agency. 
I was not notified by Experian about reinserting this account of my consumer report and according to U.S. Code 1681i ( a ) ( 5 ) ( b ) iii ) Additional information As part of, or in addition to, the notice under clause ( ii ), a consumer reporting agency shall provide to a consumer in writing not later than 5 business days after the date of the reinsertion ( I ) a statement that the disputed information has been reinserted ; ( II ) the business name and address of any furnisher of information contacted and the telephone number of such furnisher, if reasonably available, or of any furnisher of information that contacted the consumer reporting agency, in connection with the reinsertion of such information ; and ( III ) a notice that the consumer has the right to add a statement to the consumers file disputing the accuracy or completeness of the disputed information. I wasn't notified nor did I receive a statement that the disputed information was reinserted, nor was I given the business name and address of the furnisher of information contacted and the telephone number of the furnisher. This is a clear violation.

Product: Credit reporting, credit repair services, or other personal consumer reports
Sub-issue: Information belongs to someone else
Consumer complaint narrative:
To whom it May Concern, This letter is a formal complaint that you are reporting inaccurate and incomplete credit information. I am distressed that you have included the information below in my credit profile and that you have failed to maintain reasonable procedures in your operations to assure maximum possible accuracy in the credit reports you publish. Credit reporting laws ensure that bureaus report only 100 % accurate credit information. Every step must be taken to assure the information reported is completely accurate and correct. The following information therefore needs to be re-investigated. According to the Fair Credit Reporting Act, Section 609 ( a ) ( 1 ) ( A ), you are required by federal law to verify, through the physical verification of the original signed consumer contract, any and all accounts that you post on a credit report. Otherwise, anyone paying for your reporting services could fax, mail, or email in a fraudulent account. I demand to see verifiable proof ( i.e., an original consumer contract with my signature on it ) that you have on file for the account ( s ) listed below. Your failure to positively verify these accounts has hurt my ability to obtain credit. Under the FCRA, unverifiable accounts must be removed and if you are unable to provide me a copy of verifiable proof, you must remove the account ( s ) listed below. I demand that the following account ( s ) be verified or removed immediately : 1 ) XXXX XXXX XXXX Account number - XXXX Date opened- XX/XX/XXXX XXXX ) XXXX XXXX, XXXX Account number - XXXX Date opened - XX/XX/XXXX I respectfully request to be provided with proof of this alleged item ( s ), specifically the contract, note or other instrument bearing my signature failing that, the item ( s ) must be deleted from the report as soon as possible. This information is entirely inaccurate and incomplete, and as such represents a very serious error in your reporting. Please delete this misleading information and supply a corrected credit profile to all creditors who have received a copy within the last six months, or the last two years for employment purposes. Additionally, please provide the name, address, and telephone number of each credit grantor or other subscriber. Under federal law, you have thirty ( 30 ) days to complete your investigation. Be advised that the description of the procedure used to determine the accuracy and completeness of the information is hereby requested as well, to be provided within fifteen ( 15 ) days of the completion of your investigation. In addition, please remove all non-account holding inquires over 30 days old. Also, please add a promotional suppression to my credit file. Under federal law, you have 30 days to complete your re-investigation. Be advised that the description of the procedure used to determine the accuracy and completeness of the information is hereby requested as well, to be provide within fifteen ( 15 ) days of the completion of your reinvestigation. 
Thank You

On this notice it stated that added interest had started accruing in XXXX on top of the original amount that was not payed. This was the first letter I had received from the appraisal district notifying me that the property taxes had not been payed In XXXX of XXXX. This is a new home that we bought in XX/XX/XXXX. In closing we set up an Escrow account with XXXX Mortgage and put down a payment of {$1500.00} towards escrow. When the account was set up we started paying towards the escrow account monthly starting in XXXX when the first payment was due for the house. I have been dealing with XXXX customer service for a month now trying to get this issue resolved. I sent them the notice I received in the mail as well as the XXXX tax statement that we received in the mail stating what our XXXX property taxes amount owed and it states at the bottom of the statement, please do not pay original has been sent to mortgage company and it has the mortgage companys name and mailing address. For 3 weeks now customer service stated that they were at fault and they will be sending a check to the appraisal district with the added fees, and that I am not responsible for the added fees. I called customer service again on Friday XX/XX/XXXX, because I saw that a Tax Penalty was added to my account online for {$730.00} that was taken out of my escrow account. The customer service person stated that she will be putting in a work order to have that removed because they are responsible for the added fees and to call back next week to make sure it was resolved. I called XX/XX/XXXX to check on the status and I was told that now I am responsible for the added fees and I will be receiving a notice in the mail stating the reason why. I was also told that the original payment for the XXXX property tax amount was my responsibility and not theirs and that is why I am at fault. As of my statement on XX/XX/XXXX my escrow account balance is now - {$1800.00}. I also see on my online account that on XX/XX/XXXX a check was sent to me at an address that does not exist for {$3800.00}. I tried resolving this issue as well because now I dont know where that money is and can not get a straight answer. I still do not know if the mortgage company has sent a check to the appraisal district.

I never paid a security deposit, never paid first and last rent, never paid a single dime to the landlord ; all I did was sign the document. Exactly 30 days before the lease would start on XX/XX/XXXX, I told the landlord over their messaging portal that I want to exit my lease ( despite there being no exit option ). He told me no, and I said I wasn't going to pay it. I got no response back after that. Two months later at the end of XXXX, he sent me an eviction notice and charged me the full 12 months of rent ( which is illegal under Maryland 's rental code ), selling the debt to BYL Collections. I got their written notice a month later around XX/XX/XXXX, responded by certified mail that I was disputing the debt, asked them to verify it, and verified that they received it. This month when I got my monthly credit report, my score had dropped over 100 points due to their inaccurate debt collection. 

XXXX XXXX on XXXX and now the illegal collection attempt by BYL Collections are taking part in an illegal move to circumvent Covid19 restrictions handed down by the very university which acts in accordance to federal oversight and mandate for social distancing in response to the pandemic. 
Furthermore, I had acted in good faith before the pandemic and can not be held accountable for the pandemic itself or the aftermath of such a devastating ordeal. While I do not argue that I filed out the application I never paid a cent, never took possession of the property and was never evicted by anyone for any reason. Everything that has transpired has done so on paper by a company intent on bilking me of monies certainly not owed and holding over my head the ruination of my consumer credit files. 

Furthermore i am including in my documentation the code of Maryland which it is my belief and position that the landlord and by extension BYL Collections is violating, this over and above all the restrictions and federal guidelines in the application of Covid19 safety guidelines and Covid19 consumer abuse. 

I am asking that this agency intercede on my behalf, review the information and documents and contact the companies mentioned in my complaint, assuring that this issue which they have clearly not taken seriously, is rectified under the supervision of this agency. I am available to speak further on the matter and to provide any other information not provided in this complaint if any.

Sub-product: General-purpose credit card or charge card
Sub-issue: Can't use card to make purchases
Consumer complaint narrative:
This past weekend my bank went through conversion as PNC was taking over. As a previous employee the bank, I had expectations about how this was going to be handled. To say it fell very short of expectations is an understatement. Ill leave all the issues with getting funds to others because Im sure there are a lot of those. I have personally prided myself on my credit. My scores hover around 800. I have never had a transaction denied. I had worked at BBVA also and even though I worked at other banks I always used my bbva credit card due to rewards earned. I used it religiously and did not use a debit card. Well I was leaving for a trip without my family Thursday until today. So on Wednesday evening of XX/XX/XXXX I went to pay for my luggage through XXXX  XXXX  and it would not go through. I called XXXX  and after 10 minutes I was told it was declined. So first off I was not happy since I have never been more embarrassed but more importantly I had no idea why. Back up a few weeks. I looked at PNCs website with their welcome and what to expect during conversion specifically credits cards. After 29 minutes of searching. It said that I would be able to use my credit card through conversion and after conversion I would receive a new PNC card to start using upon arrival. Well I called PNC and after 25-30 minutes Im told that PNC had just created my new card and I should receive it in a few days and by the way, your old card wont work. Here I am leaving my wife and kids at home with a credit card to use, Im going away with a credit card to use and guess what, I have no access to my credit. How is this possible to post information on your website and not follow through? I still have no credit and I feel very lucky that nothing happened where I was in dire need. Im not sure what the laws state specific to credit since they had XXXX reason for me not to have access except for this cluster of a conversion. The lady I spoke to couldnt turn it back on and and told me basically I was stuck and nothing they could do. Ive never been so embarrassed and still aggravated I dont have a card. 

In addition I was not properly disclosed to about the changes. In XXXX I moved to XXXX area. I had changed my address with BBVA in XXXX. Well apparently that change did not get to PNC. A week before conversion I had to call and verify a bbva had the correct address, PNC kept sending to my old address. Also I explore someone to actually go to PNCs website and find credit card conversion. Its like the hidden ball trick. 

If I want to send an email or call someone above a basic customer service person, there is no way to route that. They dont provide that information to the public. I have attempted calling, emailing using XXXX. I complained on XXXX directly to PNC customer service and didnt get a response for 3 days Ive worked at a lot of XXXX  and have been through many conversions and this one by far was the most disorganized one with the worst communication. All my accounts will be closed and Im researching further action XXXX XXXX

Product: Mortgage
Consumer complaint narrative:
This VA backed mortgage account was under forbearance when I requested to apply for refinancing on XX/XX/XXXX. Instead, I received notice that I have until XX/XX/XXXX to come up with a lump sum payment of everything under forbearance, {$9800.00} plus any additional fees, payments and late charges that come due before that date, under threat of foreclosure proceedings on that date. 

Upon my first application for forbearance in XX/XX/XXXX, I was led to believe that the payments under forbearance would be nearly automatically placed at the back end of my mortgage, with little action on my part. Without this assurance, I never would have signed on to a forbearance agreement. 

I reached out to SunTrust now Truist on XX/XX/XXXX, as we are prompted to do in every correspondence and article, with my request for a refinance. Instead of responding to my direct request for refinance, SunTrust now Truist started the foreclosure clock ticking. They have yet to respond to ANY of my questions or requests, simply provided canned denial letters, never even acknowledging my request to refinance. 

Incidentally, although I have been reading that forbearance up to 18 months is possible, I had been allowed under 12 months protection when this demand letter came Dated XX/XX/XXXX. 

SunTrust now Truist has ignored the protections for VA mortgages under the VA mortgage loan program, the Cares Act and the American Rescue plan act in that they have refused to address my request for refinance, they are requiring me to make a lump sum payment of forbearance balance under threat of foreclosure and, although the foreclosure moratorium was extended to the end of XXXX, I am still under threat of foreclosure on XX/XX/XXXX. 

I believe I will be eligible to receive help under the American Rescue Plan Act {$10.00} XXXX dollar fund if and when Kentucky ever gets their process in place to distribute these funds. I am registered to receive notification when that happens. 

I have approximately 50 % equity in this property - my ONLY asset after the death of my veteran husband. 

My income is set to increase by approximately $ XXXX/mo in XX/XX/XXXX, on my XXXX birthday when I become eligible to collect Social Security survivors benefit. 

I have provided my plan for a cash out refinance sufficient to pay off my {$12000.00} auto loan and maintain the new mortgage payment for the 6 months until XX/XX/XXXX when XXXX benefits begin. I have worked in banking. I have made mortgages. I know this plan is perfectly doable. 

SunTrust now Truist has yet to respond to ANY of my requests to refinance OR questions about their non adherence to VA mortgage rules set out by Congress. 

I have never spoken to or received any correspondence from a loan officer. There is absolutely NO direct communication allowed for. You speak only to data processors by phone, who know nothing about the actual account. I stopped answering the telephone calls when the callers didn't even know the account was under forbearance or that I have written repeatedly. Instead, I have requested all correspondence to be in writing. Still, no acknowledgement of my request to refinance. 

I cared for my XXXX Veteran husband during his final years spent fighting XXXX XXXX attributed to his time in country exposed to XXXX XXXX. A terrible, violently painful way to die ... in service to his country. 

I ALONE cared for his every need along with all other duties and tasks while he was sick. I too, in that way, have served my country. 

I believe SunTrust now Truist should be held accountable to the promises Congress expressed through the Cares Act and the American Rescue Plan Act as well as the promises afforded by the VA mortgage loan program. 

There are millions of folks in my same situation all over the country. Banks should not be allowed AGAIN to run rough shod over the laws and regulations as they have in the past and most certainly NOT for VA mortgage loan borrowers. 

Any help in this matter would be greatly appreciated.

Consumer complaint narrative:
On XX/XX/2021, Midland Credit Management served me with a notice to appear to a pre-trial conference/mediation, alleging I owed them {$3300.00} on a credit card debt originally issued by XXXX XXXX , which they had purchased. This was the first time I heard of that alleged debt. I called their lawyer up and ask for details. The lawyer asked if I knew of an address in Kentucky, which was totally unknown to me. Upon a quick investigation with the vendor, it appeared I was victim of identity theft. I filed a report, appeared at the pre-trial conference, and submitted a Counterclaim in the Small Claims Court. The derogatory report submitted by Midland to the various CRAs resulted in StudentAid declining me a {$30000.00} Parent Plus Student Loan for my son who is in Senior year in College, and for his landlord declining me as a guarantor for his lease. My son was in mental health therapy at the time and this additional stress clearly aggravated his condition. I asked for {$8000.00} on damages.

A couple of days after the conference, Midland asked the Court to dismiss their claim, and filed a Motion to Dismiss my Counterclaim, arguing that " Courts have consistently concluded that the FCRA does not provide a private cause of action for violations of Section 1681s-2 ( a ). See 15 U.S.C. 1682s-2 ( d ) : Longman, 702 F.3d at 151 ( " [ T ] he statute plainly restricts enforcement of [ 15 U.S.C. 1681s-2 ( a ) to federal and state authorities. " ), '' and concluding " Even assuming all of the allegations were true and taken in the light most favorable to the Defendant, the Counterclaim would still fail to state any claim upon which relief may be granted under the FCRA. '' I was served with the Motion to Dismiss on XX/XX/2021. 

I have not heard from the Court yet, and I would like to know if indeed Midland 's assertion that I have no cause of action is correct. If it is, please let me know how best handle this matter in order to obtain proper redress. Thank you.

Ultimately, I ended u booking a room at the XXXX XXXX and staying there until Wednesday the XXXX. 

Upon arriving at the terminal, we were ushered in the conference room, where were instructed to complete multple training exercises via our handheld devices ; this went on the entire monday and tuesday. Furthermore, during the orentation I informed the presenter that I do not eat meat and was informed that they would provide accommodations. Dear Consumer Financial protection Bureau, I am writing to file a formal complaint against Equifax for their continued failure to delete a fraudulent account from my consumer report ( credit report ). The account in question is from XXXXXXXX XXXX XXXXXXXX, with the account number # XXXX, Stated amount {$1000.00}. 

I have already submitted a FTC Identity Theft Report, which clearly documents that this account is fraudulent and should be deleted from my consumer report. However, Equifax has refused to take any action and has continued to report this account, which has damaged my credit score and made it difficult for me to obtain credit or loans. 

Equifax 's failure to delete this fraudulent account is a direct violation of the Fair Credit Reporting Act ( FCRA ). Despite having knowledge of the fraudulent nature of this account, Equifax has not done any due diligence to investigate the information they have reported, which is a further violation of the FCRA. 

I am requesting that the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau take immediate action to hold Equifax accountable for their actions and ensure that they comply with the FCRA. I am also requesting that Equifax take immediate steps to remove the fraudulent account from my consumer report and provide me with a corrected copy of my report. 

In addition, I request that Equifax block any further attempts by the fraudulent party to create or use accounts in my name. This is necessary to protect my identity and prevent any further damage to my credit score. 

Thank you for your attention to this matter. 

Sincerely, XXXX XXXX XXXX

Consumer complaint narrative:
XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, NJ, XXXX XXXX XXXX XX/XX/2023 XXXX XXXXXXXX Attn : Customer Relations XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, UT XXXX Subject : Unauthorized Hard Inquiry on My Credit Report Dear Sir/Madam of XXXX  XXXX, I hope this letter finds you well. I am writing to address a concerning matter regarding an unauthorized hard inquiry on my credit report, which I believe to be fraudulent and in violation of the Fair Credit Reporting Act ( FCRA ). I kindly request that XXXX XXXX promptly investigate and remove this inquiry from my credit report. 

Upon reviewing my credit report, I discovered an unauthorized hard inquiry dated XX/XX/2023. I would like to emphasize that I did not authorize this inquiry nor did I have any prior knowledge of it. This unauthorized inquiry not only impacts my credit score but also raises concerns about potential fraudulent activity. 

Under the FCRA, consumers have the right to dispute any inaccurate or unauthorized information on their credit reports. According to Section 1681b of the FCRA, entities seeking access to an individual 's credit report must obtain the consumer 's written consent before pulling their credit records. As I did not provide authorization for this inquiry, I believe it is in violation of this provision. 

I kindly request that XXXX XXXX promptly investigate this matter and take appropriate action to remove the unauthorized hard inquiry from my credit report. I also request that you provide me with a written confirmation once the inquiry has been removed. 

Enclosed with this letter, please find a screenshot of my credit report highlighting the unauthorized hard inquiry for your reference. I trust that you will handle this matter promptly and in accordance with the law. If necessary, I am prepared to take further action to protect my rights under the FCRA. 

I look forward to your prompt attention to this matter. Please contact me at your earliest convenience to discuss the steps being taken to resolve this issue. Thank you for your cooperation. 

Yours sincerely, XXXX XXXX

Consumer complaint narrative:
I have been a Bank of America credit card holder for many years. 
I received a statement in XXXX this year showing a transaction of XXXX dollars charged to my credit card from XXXX, XXXX. 
Transaction date was XX/XX/XXXX and posting date XX/XX/XXXX. 
I visited XXXX in XXXX and I have not been out of country or in XXXX since then. 
I did not lose my credit card and it has been with me. 
I called the Bank on XX/XX/XXXX and talked for a long time and told the detail. 
On XX/XX/XXXX I received a letter saying that the card was used and chip was read that time and so it was a valid claim. 
I called the Bank at the # provided and they called back my cell #. 
I talked to the specialist and the supervisor as they allowed me to talk to for over XXXX minutes. I tried to talk to someone higher up in the authority who can help to further investigate this fraudulent claim but was not able to. 
I asked whether there was any transaction in that card in XXXX in XXXX but they refused to give me that information. 
I have not been to XXXX or anywhere else outside XXXX in XXXX or XXXX and the card was with me. So it was impossible to use my card in XXXX in XXXX XXXX. 
They could not explain how the chip was read or the card used when I had not been there and the card was with me and no duplicate copy of the card. 
They did not give me any convincing reason how it could be possible. 
They did not give any answer how they investigated the fraud claim and whether any federal or law enforcing agency was involved as this seems to me a certain fraud case. 
They could not explain why they approve a very unusual foreign transaction without verification and without contacting or verifying with the card holder. 
I always notify the credit card company if I am going out of State or out of Country, and they did not receive any such notifications / alert from me.

Given the unusual nature of this transaction I asked whether anyone in the company could be associated with this kind of fraudulent activity, which they did not answer and did not say whether any law enforcing agency involved in that regard. 
They said they would open another investigation to look into the matter. 
I received another letter dated XX/XX/XXXX saying that they found it was a valid transaction and the fraud claim was closed. 
Now given that I could not be there in XXXX to use my credit card and it was always with me, yet the company / Bank of America maintained that it was a valid transaction - it raised a serious question whether the credit card company be involved in this fraudulent activity and whether they or others involved in activities defrauding their credit card holders. 
I called the Bank of America again on XX/XX/XXXX and asked for my options and provide me with the names of the State and federal regulatory agencies or other Law enforcing Agencies where I can take this case for further review but I was told to XXXX it and they could not provide me any. 
They have defrauded XXXX dollars of me and foreign currency transaction fees with this credit card fraud and wonder whether this is a systemic issue with the credit card business. 
I will appreciate any of your help in this regard and also to further this with any Law Enforcing Agencies for a deeper investigation if and as necessary to protect us the consumers.
